description: The xzibit_apps dataset provides detailed information about various machine learning-assisted labeling applications. Each entry in the dataset represents an application, capturing essential metadata and usage characteristics. This dataset is particularly useful for developers and data scientists who are interested in understanding the deployment and characteristics of these applications. Key features include the application ID, version, and descriptive labels, which help in identifying and categorizing the apps. The dataset also includes information about the visibility and usage of the applications, such as whether they are limited in visibility, used as a recipe, or have associated images. Additionally, the dataset tracks the origin of the application and the number of instances deployed, providing insights into the application's reach and usage. The short descriptions offer a narrative about the creation and purpose of each app, enhancing the understanding of its functionality. This dataset is valuable for managing and analyzing the deployment of machine learning tools in various environments, facilitating better decision-making and optimization of resources.
shortDesc: Dataset of ML-assisted labeling apps with metadata and usage details.

columns.name: onlyLimitedVisibility
columns.comment: Indicates if app has limited visibility, boolean value.

columns.name: appId
columns.comment: Unique identifier for the application, includes plugin name.

columns.name: appVersion
columns.comment: Version information of the application, often 'N/A'.

columns.name: label
columns.comment: Descriptive label for the application, free text.

columns.name: shortDesc
columns.comment: Detailed description of the app, includes creation info.

columns.name: tags
columns.comment: Tags associated with the app, stored as JSON array.

columns.name: isAppImg
columns.comment: Indicates if app has an associated image, boolean value.

columns.name: origin
columns.comment: Source or origin of the application, often 'PLUGIN'.

columns.name: instanceCount
columns.comment: Number of instances of the app deployed, integer value.

columns.name: useAsRecipe
columns.comment: Indicates if app can be used as a recipe, boolean value.
